729700f-a.title: Richmond: State Street - Castleton Avenue
729700f-a.text:
85 State Street, east side, between Castleton Avenue
and Noale Place, showing the West New Brighton sub-branch of
the New York Public Library. The sub-branch moved to the above
address from 848 Castleton Avenue in 1923. In 1932 the sub-branch
became a branch of the New York Public Library and moved into
new quarters at 976 Castleton Avenue.
1924
P. L. Sperr

728662f-a.title: Richmond: Castleton Avenue - State Street
728662f-a.text:
Castleton Ate., north side (houses thereon), east from State
Street to Broadway. The view is from State Street.
March 24, 1930.
P. L. Sperr.
